# Architecture & Development Rules

## Core Principles

- **Server-first:** Default to React Server Components. Only add `"use client"` when the component requires browser APIs, event handlers, or hooks. Never make a `page.tsx` a client component.
- **Single source of truth:** Every piece of logic, type, or configuration exists in exactly one place. No duplication.
- **Explicit over implicit:** No `any` types. No untyped props. Explicit return types on all exported functions.
- **Co-location:** Feature-specific code lives next to the feature page. Shared code lives in `src/lib/`, `src/hooks/`, `src/components/`, `src/types/`, or `src/utils/`.
- **Thin pages:** `page.tsx` files are composition-only shells. Zero business logic, no hooks, no state.

## Folder Structure

```
src/app/(admin)/[feature]/
  page.tsx                  # Server component, composition only
  [Feature].tsx             # Main client component (PascalCase)
  use-[feature].ts          # Feature context hook (createAppContext)
  actions/[feature].actions.ts   # Server actions ("use server" required)
  types/[feature].types.ts       # Feature types
  schemas/[feature].schemas.ts   # Zod schemas
  components/[Sub].tsx           # Feature sub-components
```

- New admin features go under `src/app/(admin)/[feature-name]/`.
- New UI primitives go in `src/components/ui/` and are registered in `src/components/index.ts`.
- New form wrappers go in `src/components/form/` and are registered in `src/components/index.ts`.
- Shared logic goes in `src/lib/[domain]/`.
- NEVER put feature-specific logic in `src/lib/`, `src/hooks/`, or `src/utils/`.

## Component Rules

- **Dumb (presentational):** `src/components/ui/*`, `src/components/form/*`. Props in, UI out. No data fetching.
- **Smart (feature):** `src/app/(admin)/[feature]/[Feature].tsx`. Consume context, call actions.
- **Pages:** Composition only. No hooks, no state, no logic.
- Components over 150 lines MUST be split into sub-components.
- All props use named TypeScript types. Children: `React.ReactNode`, never `any`.

## State Management

- Server state: Fetch in Server Components or server actions. Pass as props.
- Feature state: `createAppContext` factory. One provider per feature in `page.tsx`.
- Local UI state: `useState`/`useReducer` in the owning component.
- URL state: `nuqs` for persistent/shareable state (filters, pagination).
- NEVER fetch server data in `useEffect`. Use server components or event-driven server actions.
- If global client state is needed, use Zustand. No Redux, no Jotai.

## Data & API Layer

- Server actions (`*.actions.ts`): Must have `"use server"` directive, return `Response<T>`, call `isAuthenticated()` from `@/lib/auth/isAuthenticated` for protected features, use `handleResponse()`.
- API routes: Reserved for external integrations (webhooks, OAuth). Internal data uses server actions.
- Prisma: Always import from `@/lib/prisma/client`. Never instantiate new clients.

## Naming Conventions

| Entity | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Feature folder | kebab-case | `booking-forms/` |
| Component file | PascalCase | `Dashboard.tsx` |
| Hook file | `use-[name].ts` | `use-dashboard.ts` |
| Action file | `[feature].actions.ts` | `dashboard.actions.ts` |
| Type file | `[feature].types.ts` | `dashboard.types.ts` |
| Schema file | `[feature].schemas.ts` | `lead.schemas.ts` |
| Type/Interface | PascalCase, NO `I` prefix | `MenuItem` not `IMenuItem` |
| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `EXCLUDED_PAGES` |
| Booleans | `is`/`has`/`should` prefix | `isAuthenticated` |

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS only via `className`.
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional classes.
- Use `cva` for component variants.
- NEVER use inline `style={{}}` (exception: truly dynamic computed values).
- NEVER create `.module.css` files.
- NEVER add component CSS classes in `globals.css`.

## Error Handling

- Server actions: `try/catch` around DB ops, return `Response<T>` with `status: 'error'`. Never throw.
- Client: Check `response.status`, display via `toast.error()` from sonner. Forms use `form.setError()`.
- Route groups MUST have `error.tsx` boundaries and `loading.tsx` fallbacks.
- NEVER silently swallow errors or show raw error messages to users.

## Anti-Patterns (FORBIDDEN)

- `any` types on props, return values, or data
- Fetching in `useEffect` + storing in `useState` for server data
- Middleware calling its own API routes
- Commented-out code checked in
- Duplicate barrel re-exports
- Copy-paste naming errors (component name must match purpose)
- `@ts-ignore` without justification (use `@ts-expect-error` with comment)
- Action files missing `"use server"` directive
- Duplicate implementations of the same logic
